WEBVTT

00:07.008 --> 00:09.169
[ FIRE CRACKLING ]

00:15.266 --> 00:17.131
[HORSE NEIGHS]

00:20.188 --> 00:21.928
[HORSES NEIGHING]

00:29.906 --> 00:33.615
[ SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE ]

00:33.826 --> 00:39.617
WALT, THE OLD MAN SAYS,
"THIS WAY OF LIFE IS NOT EASY."

00:39.832 --> 00:43.416
IT IS A WAY OF LIFE
FOR THE STRONG HEART.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.167
[HORSE NEIGHS]

00:58.976 --> 01:02.685
"THIS SACRED LODGE
IS OUR ORIGINAL HOME

01:02.897 --> 01:04.057
FROM OUR MOTHER EARTH."

01:04.273 --> 01:06.229
"COMING IN,

01:06.442 --> 01:08.558
YOU WILL LEAVE BEHIND
ALL THAT IS BAD."

01:12.073 --> 01:13.313
[HORSE NEIGHING]

01:25.169 --> 01:26.875
[ SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE ]

01:27.088 --> 01:29.329
"STAY TRUE
TO YOUR WARRIOR SPIRIT."

01:31.092 --> 01:32.673
"KNOW WHEN TO FIGHT
AND WHEN TO --"

01:32.885 --> 01:35.126
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

01:39.141 --> 01:40.642
[WALT SIGHS 1

01:40.851 --> 01:43.183
THIS IS WHY
I DON'T HAVE A CELLPHONE.

01:45.856 --> 01:47.562
RUBEN, DO NOT
BRING THAT PHONE IN HERE.

01:47.775 --> 01:49.436
IT'S FOR THE SHERIFF.

02:03.916 --> 02:06.874
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

02:12.967 --> 02:17.757
[ DOOR BEEPING ]

02:59.597 --> 03:02.885
I WAS STARTING TO WORRY
ABOUT YOU, SHERIFF.

03:03.100 --> 03:05.967
SHE THE ONLY HORSE
THAT MADE IT OUT?

03:06.187 --> 03:07.973
LOOKS THAT WAY.

03:08.189 --> 03:10.396
FOR SURE THERE ARE
TWO DEAD HORSES INSIDE.

03:10.608 --> 03:12.098
THIS ONE HERE'S LIKELY
TO BE THE THIRD,

03:12.318 --> 03:13.649
GIVEN THE SEVERITY
OF THE BURNS.

03:15.237 --> 03:17.319
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

03:17.531 --> 03:18.907
[ SNORTS 1

03:19.116 --> 03:21.903
DON'T YOU
LISTEN TO BRANCH.

03:25.498 --> 03:27.910
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

03:32.505 --> 03:34.791
WHAT A SHIT STORM.

03:35.007 --> 03:37.749
[ SIGHS 1
THAT BILL HOBACK?

03:37.968 --> 03:38.923
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

03:39.136 --> 03:40.342
HE'S THE STEWARTS'
NEIGHBOR.

03:40.554 --> 03:42.340
HE LIVES
FIVE MILES THAT WAY.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.342
BUT HE SAW THE LIGHTS,
HEARD THE SIRENS,

03:44.558 --> 03:46.264
AND CAME OVER TO SEE
IF HE COULD HELP.

03:46.477 --> 03:47.466
WHERE'S RAY?

03:47.687 --> 03:50.303
THE HUSBAND?
NOBODY SEEMS TO KNOW.

03:50.523 --> 03:52.184
[ SIGHS ] THAT'S HIS TRUCK
OVER THERE.

03:52.400 --> 03:54.231
YEAH. I'VE BEEN
CALLING HIS CELL ALL NIGHT.

03:54.443 --> 03:56.855
NO ANSWER.

03:57.071 --> 03:59.278
EXCUSE ME.
SHERIFF LONGMIRE?

03:59.490 --> 04:01.151
I THINK
THERE'S A BODY INSIDE.

04:01.367 --> 04:03.153
I MEAN, IT'S HARD TO TELL
WITH THE SMOKE AND THE ASH,

04:03.369 --> 04:04.734
AND THAT ROOF
COULD COME DOWN ANY SECOND.

04:04.954 --> 04:06.364
YOU CAN'T GO IN.
IT'S JUST NOT SAFE.

04:06.580 --> 04:07.956
IT'S BETTER
TO WAIT UNTIL MORNING.

04:08.165 --> 04:10.417
IF THERE'S A BODY IN THERE,
THEN WE'RE GOING INSIDE.

04:10.626 --> 04:12.787
NO. WE ARE NOT.

04:13.003 --> 04:14.209
I AM.

04:14.422 --> 04:16.413
SHERIFF,
AT LEAST WEAR MY HAT.

04:16.632 --> 04:19.089
NO, THANKS.
I GOT ONE.

04:45.286 --> 04:47.447
[ GRUNTING 1

04:51.959 --> 04:54.291
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

04:56.338 --> 04:57.839
HEY, BILL.

04:58.048 --> 05:03.259
CAN YOU TAKE T.J. INSIDE
FOR A FEW MINUTES?

05:03.471 --> 05:04.881
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:05.097 --> 05:08.089
T.J., WHY DON'T YOU, UH,
HELP ME FIND SOMETHING TO EAT

05:08.309 --> 05:10.391
FOR ALL THESE
FIREFIGHTERS HERE?

05:10.603 --> 05:11.592
IT'S OKAY.

05:11.812 --> 05:13.598
LET'S SEE
WHAT YOU GOT INSIDE.

05:16.150 --> 05:18.937
RAY IS GONNA
BE DEVASTATED.

05:22.573 --> 05:24.655
HE LOVES THOSE HORSES.
THEY'RE HIS LIFE.

05:24.867 --> 05:26.698
HAVE YOU BEEN
ABLE TO REACH RAY?

05:26.911 --> 05:28.697
I LEFT HIM MESSAGES
ON HIS CELL.

05:28.913 --> 05:30.119
NO.

05:41.634 --> 05:44.546
WHERE DID
YOU GET THAT?

05:45.971 --> 05:48.462
IN THE BARN.
I'M AFRAID --

05:48.682 --> 05:51.424
THAT'S HIS WATCH!

05:51.644 --> 05:54.056
OH, GOD.

05:54.271 --> 05:58.765
[VOICE BREAKING]
OH, GOD. NO.

05:58.984 --> 06:03.193
[GRYING 1 OH, GOD. OH, GOD.
OH, GOD, WHAT HAPPENED?!

06:03.405 --> 06:05.612
THE SUN IS GONNA COME UP,
AND WHEN IT DOES,

06:05.825 --> 06:07.235
I PROMISE TO FIND OUT.

06:07.451 --> 06:12.662
NO. [ CRYING ]
OH, MY GOD.

06:12.873 --> 06:17.412
OH, MY GOD.

06:17.628 --> 06:19.038
[ CRYING 1

06:25.928 --> 06:27.008
T.J.!

06:27.221 --> 06:28.631
SHE NEEDS
TO BE PUT DOWN.

06:28.848 --> 06:30.839
HOLD UP.
T.J., LET'S TALK!

06:31.058 --> 06:34.471
SON,
PUT DOWN THE GUN!
HE'S OKAY. HE'S OKAY.

06:39.316 --> 06:42.183
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
EASY, EASY.

06:42.403 --> 06:43.813
NO, IT'S SELFISH
TO KEEP HER ALIVE

06:44.029 --> 06:45.018
WHEN SHE'S LIKE THIS.

06:45.239 --> 06:47.104
MOVE OUT OF THE WAY.
[ GUN COCKS]

06:48.993 --> 06:50.449
NO!
[GUNSHOT]

07:10.723 --> 07:12.213
[VIC SNIFFS]

07:12.433 --> 07:14.515
[SIGHS]

07:19.940 --> 07:22.101
ROOM SERVICE.

07:23.485 --> 07:25.567
YOU KNOW, I'VE SEEN
SOME MESSED UP SHIT ON THE JOB,

07:25.779 --> 07:27.690
BUT THIS IS
MY FIRST HORSE FIRE.

07:27.907 --> 07:29.772
SURE AS HELL
HOPE IT'S MY LAST.

07:42.838 --> 07:44.544
WINSTON CHURCHILL
ONCE SAID,

07:44.757 --> 07:49.342
"THE OUTSIDE OF A HORSE IS
GOOD FOR THE INSIDE OF A MAN."

07:51.931 --> 07:54.798
THIS GUY
RAISE RACEHORSES?

07:55.017 --> 07:56.598
NOPE. CUTTING HORSES.

07:58.812 --> 08:00.313
ALL THOSE TROPHIES --

08:00.522 --> 08:03.514
THESE HORSES
MUST HAVE BEEN WORTH A LOT.

08:03.734 --> 08:05.395
BODY'S OVER THERE
UNDER THOSE STAIRS.

08:05.611 --> 08:07.897
[COUGHS]

08:14.203 --> 08:18.367
NOW I SEE WHY
RAY DIDN'T ANSWER HIS CELLPHONE.

08:24.171 --> 08:27.083
[ CLATTERING 1

08:28.842 --> 08:31.549
.45.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.884
ALL THE ROUNDS
WENT OFF.

08:37.101 --> 08:40.764
BUT ONLY ONE SPENT PRIMER,
SO ONE ROUND WAS FIRED,

08:40.980 --> 08:43.187
AND THE OTHERS
EXPLODED FROM THE HEAT.

08:43.399 --> 08:45.606
I'M GUESSING HE TOOK ONE
TO THE HEAD.

08:49.613 --> 08:51.569
GIVE ME A HAND HERE.

08:56.870 --> 08:59.156
GOING UP?
YEP.

08:59.373 --> 09:00.829
[BOTH GRUNT]

09:01.041 --> 09:02.781
PADLOCK
ON THE INSIDE.

09:03.002 --> 09:04.117
[ CHAIN RATTLES ]

09:04.336 --> 09:05.951
LOOKS LIKE RAY

09:06.171 --> 09:08.628
DIDN'T WANT ANYONE
TO GET INSIDE TO HELP HIM.

09:08.841 --> 09:11.332
LOOKS THAT WAY.

09:15.264 --> 09:18.097
ALICE: WHAT HAVE YOU FOUND?
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:18.308 --> 09:20.264
IT'S STILL EARLY,
MRS. STEWART.

09:20.477 --> 09:22.809
BUT I CALLED A FRIEND
OF MINE FROM THE INSURANCE
COMPANY TO COME OUT,

09:23.022 --> 09:25.934
TAKE A LOOK AROUND,
AND HELP US SORT THIS OUT, SO...

09:26.150 --> 09:28.106
NOW, THERE WILL
LIKELY BE AN AUTOPSY.

09:28.318 --> 09:30.229
I'LL PUSH TO
HAVE THAT HAPPEN TODAY.

09:30.446 --> 09:31.777
THANK YOU.

09:31.989 --> 09:34.901
SO, WAS RAY UNDER
ANY PARTICULAR PRESSURE LATELY?

09:35.117 --> 09:37.904
HE WAS --
HE WAS PREPARING

09:38.120 --> 09:39.906
FOR A BIG COMPETITION
IN HOUSTON.

09:41.206 --> 09:43.037
HE LOVED THOSE HORSES.

09:44.668 --> 09:46.204
BUT...

09:46.420 --> 09:48.035
WHAT?

09:48.255 --> 09:52.248
WELL, LAST WEEK HE --
HE ASKED A DOCTOR

09:52.468 --> 09:54.459
TO PRESCRIBE HIM
SOME ANTIDEPRESSANTS.

09:54.678 --> 09:56.669
I FOR-- I FORGET THE NAME,
BUT I THINK THEY'RE UPSTAIRS

09:56.889 --> 09:58.470
IN THE MEDICINE CABINET.

09:58.682 --> 10:03.392
UH, DEPUTY MORETTI,
WOULD YOU...?

10:07.941 --> 10:11.229
SO, ALICE...

10:11.445 --> 10:13.276
YOU KNOW I HAVE TO
ASK YOU ABOUT IT.

10:13.489 --> 10:15.229
SORRY. ABOUT WHAT?

10:15.449 --> 10:17.030
YOU CAME TO ME
TWO YEARS AGO.

10:17.242 --> 10:19.028
THAT WAS
A MISUNDERSTANDING.

10:19.244 --> 10:20.359
HE HIT YOU.

10:20.579 --> 10:21.989
I KNOW YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO PRESS CHARGES,

10:22.206 --> 10:23.821
BUT YOU TOLD ME
HE HIT YOU.

10:24.041 --> 10:26.657
SO I HAVE TO ASK --
WAS IT HAPPENING AGAIN?

10:26.877 --> 10:28.162
THAT WAS
A ONE-TIME THING.

10:28.378 --> 10:31.711
I SWEAR, SHERIFF.
RAY LOVED ME.

10:31.924 --> 10:33.539
NOW, YOU ASKED ME
TO KEEP IT A SECRET.

10:33.759 --> 10:36.375
AND I HAVE.
BUT I NEED TO KNOW --

10:36.595 --> 10:39.007
DID ANYBODY ELSE
KNOW ABOUT THAT INCIDENT?

10:40.516 --> 10:41.471
SAY, T.J.?

10:44.228 --> 10:45.934
WHAT IS IT,
SWEETHEART?

10:46.146 --> 10:47.932
I WAS GOING THROUGH
DAD'S DESK

10:48.148 --> 10:50.764
AND I FOUND THIS NOTE
UNDERNEATH THE KEYBOARD.

10:52.444 --> 10:54.935
MY NAME WAS ON THE ENVELOPE,
AND YOURS WAS, TOO.

11:06.708 --> 11:08.790
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:09.002 --> 11:11.459
I'M SO SORRY.

11:18.762 --> 11:21.674
OH. IS THIS
RAY'S SIGNATURE?

11:21.890 --> 11:24.381
YES.

11:28.063 --> 11:30.645
[GRUNTS]

11:33.902 --> 11:35.642
IT'S GETTING HARD
TO SEE THIS

11:35.863 --> 11:37.819
AS ANYTHING OTHER
THAN A SUICIDE.

11:39.867 --> 11:42.153
NOT MUCH
OF A SUICIDE NOTE.

11:42.369 --> 11:44.576
"I'M SORRY
FOR EVERYTHING I'VE DONE.

11:44.788 --> 11:47.120
I LOVE YOU."

11:47.332 --> 11:50.950
MAN OF FEW WORDS.

11:51.170 --> 11:53.877
I KNOW THE TYPE.

12:00.637 --> 12:04.175
WHAT?

12:04.391 --> 12:07.724
I UNDERSTAND A MAN
WANTING TO KILL HIMSELF.

12:07.936 --> 12:11.929
GOT TO GO TO A PRETTY DARK PLACE
TO TAKE HIS HORSES WITH HIM.

12:24.286 --> 12:26.242
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

12:28.248 --> 12:30.580
SHERIFF.

12:30.792 --> 12:31.998
[SIGHS]

12:32.211 --> 12:33.997
YOU MIND GIVING ME A HAND
WITH HER DRESSINGS?

12:34.213 --> 12:35.328
SURE.

12:40.135 --> 12:42.842
SHOES SHOULD HAVE BEEN CHANGED
A MONTH AGO.

12:43.055 --> 12:44.966
OH, YOU KNOW A LITTLE BIT
ABOUT HORSES?

12:45.182 --> 12:46.968
I GREW UP WITH HORSES.

12:47.184 --> 12:48.424
MY DAD WAS A FARRIER.

12:48.644 --> 12:49.975
I FOLLOWED HIM AROUND,

12:50.187 --> 12:51.552
MANAGED TO PICK UP
A THING OR TWO.

12:51.772 --> 12:52.852
CHECK OUT HER TEETH.

13:01.073 --> 13:03.655
TEETH
HAVEN'T BEEN FLOATED.

13:05.035 --> 13:06.320
RAY STEWART,
BY ALL ACCOUNTS,

13:06.536 --> 13:08.322
WAS A PRETTY SERIOUS
HORSEMAN.

13:08.538 --> 13:10.574
WON QUITE A FEW TROPHIES.

13:10.791 --> 13:12.577
SOMETIMES IF THE HORSES
STOP WINNING,

13:12.793 --> 13:14.499
THE OWNERS STOP
TAKING CARE OF THEM.

13:14.711 --> 13:18.249
SO, Doc,
SHE GONNA MAKE IT?

13:18.465 --> 13:20.296
SHE'S HAD
SOME PRETTY BAD LUCK.

13:20.509 --> 13:22.591
BURNS OVER 50%
OF HER BODY,

13:22.803 --> 13:24.668
AND WHO KNOWS WHAT
SORT OF DAMAGE TO THE LUNGS.

13:24.888 --> 13:28.346
WELL, I ALWAYS
PREFER THE LONG SHOTS.

13:28.558 --> 13:32.301
SO WHATEVER IT COSTS,
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

13:32.521 --> 13:34.682
YOU SEND THE BILL
TO ME.

13:43.031 --> 13:45.898
RU BY.

13:46.118 --> 13:48.734
SHERIFF,
BEFORE YOU SAY ANYTHING,

13:48.954 --> 13:51.161
I KNOW I WAS SUPPOSED TO
BE THERE LAST NIGHT,

13:51.373 --> 13:54.991
AND THE THING IS I WAS --
WHERE MY CAMPSITE WAS,

13:55.210 --> 13:57.701
I DIDN'T HAVE
ANY CELL RECEPTION.

13:57.921 --> 14:00.788
UH,
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

14:01.008 --> 14:05.001
FERG, I WASN'T GONNA
SAY ANYTHING.

14:05.220 --> 14:08.303
BRANCH: HEY, WALT,
I SAW ONE OF YOUR CAMPAIGN SIGNS

14:10.142 --> 14:13.134
I LIKE THEM.
KIND OF OLD-SCHOOL.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.469
I PREFER
THE WORD "SUBTLE."

14:15.689 --> 14:16.849
[LAUGHS]

14:17.065 --> 14:19.226
YOU,UH,
CHECK THAT SUICIDE NOTE YET?

14:19.443 --> 14:21.058
I WENT AHEAD
AND GOT A COPY

14:21.278 --> 14:23.018
OF RAY STEWART'S SIGNATURE
FROM THE DMV,

14:23.238 --> 14:25.820
BUT I COULDN'T FIND ANY MORE
SUBSTANTIAL HANDWRITING SAMPLES

14:26.033 --> 14:27.398
TO COMPARE
THE SUICIDE NOTE TO.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.198
BANK'S GOT
MORTGAGE APPLICATIONS.

14:29.411 --> 14:32.323
COUNTY OFFICE SHOULD HAVE A COPY
OF THE DEED TO HIS RANCH, SO...

14:32.539 --> 14:34.154
[ CHUCKLES 1
LIKE THIS?

14:34.374 --> 14:35.489
[ PAPER RUSTLES ]

14:35.709 --> 14:37.040
THE RANCH IS
IN ALICE STEWART'S NAME,

14:37.252 --> 14:38.958
AND THERE IS NO MORTGAGE
APPLICATION. THEY PAID CASH.

14:39.171 --> 14:40.627
VIC: FOR THE TRUCK
AND HORSE TRAILER, TOO.

14:40.839 --> 14:42.420
UTILITY BILLS
ARE IN ALICE'S NAME.

14:42.632 --> 14:44.964
YOU KNOW, MAYBE SHE WAS THE ONE
WITH ALL THE DOUGH.

14:45.177 --> 14:46.508
BUT FOR WHATEVER REASON,

14:46.720 --> 14:48.460
RAY'S SIGNATURE
ISN'T ON ANY OF THE DOCUMENTS.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.090
I WAS THINKING WE SHOULD
GET IN TOUCH

14:50.307 --> 14:51.296
WITH THAT FBI
HANDWRITING ANALYST

14:51.516 --> 14:52.892
DOWN IN DENVER.

14:53.101 --> 14:56.184
NAH, NOT WORTH THE HASSLE
OF INVOLVING THE FBI JUST YET.

14:57.272 --> 14:58.887
ONCE THEY GET A FOOT
IN THE DOOR...

14:59.107 --> 15:01.439
NOTHING WRONG WITH A LITTLE
FRIENDLY COMPETITION, WALT.

15:01.651 --> 15:03.812
WALT: LOOKS LIKE
RAY'S HANDWRITING.

15:04.029 --> 15:05.894
HIS WIFE AND SON
SAYS IT WAS,

15:06.114 --> 15:09.231
SO UNTIL I HAVE REASON
TO SUSPECT OTHERWISE --

15:09.451 --> 15:11.362
[ DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE ]
KNOCK, KNOCK!

15:11.578 --> 15:13.614
LOOK, I'M JUST
AN INSURANCE SALESMAN,

15:13.830 --> 15:15.661
BUT I DON'T SEE WHAT IT COULD BE
OTHER THAN SUICIDE.

15:15.874 --> 15:17.705
THE DOOR WAS CHAINED
ON THE INSIDE.

15:17.918 --> 15:21.627
DID HIS LIFE INSURANCE
HAVE A SUICIDE CLAUSE?

15:21.838 --> 15:22.998
NO.

15:23.215 --> 15:25.957
BECAUSE HE DIDN'T
HAVE ANY LIFE INSURANCE.

15:26.176 --> 15:28.758
AND THE STEWARTS' HOUSE
AND BARN STRUCTURES

15:28.970 --> 15:30.506
WEREN'T INSURED,
EITHER.

15:30.722 --> 15:32.508
THE ONLY
POLICIES THEY HAD

15:32.724 --> 15:34.715
WAS A LIFE-INSURANCE POLICY
ON ALICE,

15:34.935 --> 15:36.891
NAMING T.J.
THE SOLE BENEFICIARY,

15:37.104 --> 15:39.015
AND POLICY
ON ALL OF THE HORSES.

15:39.231 --> 15:40.721
BIG POLICIES
ON THE HORSES.

15:40.941 --> 15:42.522
A COUPLE MILLION,
ALL TOLD.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.774
THOSE WERE TOP-BREED
QUARTER HORSES,

15:47.989 --> 15:50.241
AND RAY HAD
MOSTLY MARES.

15:50.450 --> 15:52.236
THEY'RE EASIER TO HANDLE
THAN THE STALLIONS.

15:54.246 --> 15:55.736
YEAH.

15:55.956 --> 15:57.992
PLUS, WHEN THEY'RE
DONE COMPETING,

15:58.208 --> 16:00.449
THEY MAKE
MILLION-DOLLAR BABIES.

16:00.669 --> 16:01.829
IT'S A DAMN SHAME,
WALT, REALLY.

16:03.588 --> 16:05.453
HEY, CAN I GET A COPY
OF YOUR EVIDENCE INVENTORY

16:05.674 --> 16:06.709
FOR MY CLAIMS REPORT?

16:06.925 --> 16:08.210
SURE.

16:08.427 --> 16:12.796
SO, WHO WAS THE BENEFICIARY
OF THE HORSE INSURANCE?

16:13.014 --> 16:14.390
ALICE.

16:17.936 --> 16:19.221
BILL: I'M GETTING YOU
IN THERE. GONNA...

16:19.438 --> 16:21.053
I'M GETTING
A FULL BODY SHOT THERE.

16:21.273 --> 16:22.888
HEY,JUST--
[LAUGHS]

16:23.108 --> 16:24.473
DON'T TELL --
DON'T TELL RAY THAT,

16:24.693 --> 16:27.480
BUT I'M GETTING --
WHOA. WHOA, BE CAREFUL.

16:27.696 --> 16:28.902
LOOK AT THE CAMERA.

16:29.114 --> 16:30.900
NO, BE CAREFUL.
YOU'RE SCARING HIM.

16:31.116 --> 16:33.323
[LAUGHS]

16:33.535 --> 16:36.527
WHOO! T.J.'S A BORN COWBOY.
YOU KIDDING ME?

16:36.746 --> 16:37.952
BILL:
GOOD RIDING, T.J.

16:38.165 --> 16:39.280
ALICE: HEY, BILL,
GIVE ME THE CAMERA.

16:39.499 --> 16:40.909
No. NO.
YEAH. [ LAUGHS]

16:41.126 --> 16:42.832
I WANT TO GET YOU
IN THIS MOVIE SOMEWHERE.

16:43.044 --> 16:44.659
NO, I DON'T WANT TO
BE IN THIS -- [ LAUGHS]

16:44.880 --> 16:46.120
RAY: WHAT WAS THAT?
OKAY.

16:46.339 --> 16:48.330
YEAH, YEAH, LOOK AT YOU.
VERY HANDSOME.

16:48.550 --> 16:51.337
COME HERE.
LET'S GET THE THREE AMIGOS.

16:51.553 --> 16:53.418
WHOO, LOOK!
ON THREE,
LET'S SAY "COWBOY."

16:53.638 --> 16:55.924
ONE, TWO, THREE...
ALL: COWBOYI

16:56.141 --> 16:57.381
WHOO!

16:57.601 --> 16:59.091
ANOTHER BEAUTIFUL DAY
IN WYOMING.

17:03.023 --> 17:06.732
HE WON THIS ONE JUST, UH,
IN VEGAS AT A COMPETITION...

17:06.943 --> 17:08.149
ALICE.
...LAST YEAR.

17:08.361 --> 17:09.271
PLEASE.

17:09.488 --> 17:10.728
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'RE DOING IT

17:10.947 --> 17:12.483
FOR YOUR BENEFIT OR MINE,
BUT RIGHT NOW

17:12.699 --> 17:13.905
I JUST NEED YOU
TO STOP LYING.

17:14.117 --> 17:15.618
EXCUSE ME?

17:15.827 --> 17:17.818
I REALIZED I NEVER SAW RAY
OR ANY OF HIS HORSES

17:18.038 --> 17:21.701
COMPETE LOCALLY,
SO I CALLED VEGAS AND AMARILLO.

17:21.917 --> 17:24.078
RAY DIDN'T WIN
ANY TROPHIES.

17:24.294 --> 17:27.036
THERE WASN'T EVEN A RECORD OF
HIM ENTERING THE COMPETITIONS.

17:27.255 --> 17:29.792
IT'S A LIE.
NO, NO. THAT CAN'T BE.

17:30.008 --> 17:31.999
AND YOUR MARE, THE ONE
THAT SURVIVED THE FIRE?

17:32.219 --> 17:34.926
SHE'D BEEN
NEGLECTED FOR MONTHS.
NO, HE LOVED THOSE HORSES.

17:35.138 --> 17:37.345
WELL, HE SURE TOOK OUT
A LOT OF INSURANCE ON 'EM.

17:37.557 --> 17:38.888
OR RATHER, YOU DID.

17:39.100 --> 17:40.385
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
SHERIFF?

17:40.602 --> 17:43.184
I'M TRYING TO GET YOU
TO TELL ME THE TRUTH.

17:43.396 --> 17:44.977
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU'RE NOT TELLING ME ABOUT RAY.

17:45.190 --> 17:47.181
N-NO, THERE ISN'T.
I SWEAR.

17:47.400 --> 17:50.267
FINE. IF THAT'S THE CASE,
YOU'RE GONNA BE CHARGED
WITH MURDERING RAY.

17:50.487 --> 17:54.025
[ SCOFFS ] WHAT?
WHY WOULD I --

17:54.241 --> 17:56.106
BECAUSE YOUR HUSBAND
BEAT YOU.

17:58.286 --> 18:00.368
OR BECAUSE YOU HAVE
LARGE INSURANCE POLICIES

18:00.580 --> 18:02.571
ON HIS HORSES,
AND YOU WANTED THAT MONEY...

18:02.791 --> 18:04.372
I TOLD YOU --
....FOR YOU AND T.J.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.996
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
HE COMMITTED SUICIDE.

18:07.212 --> 18:08.327
HE LEFT A NOTE.

18:08.547 --> 18:09.832
THAT COULD BE FORGED.

18:10.048 --> 18:12.960
H-HE CHAINED HIMSELF IN.
YOU SAID SO YOURSELF.

18:13.176 --> 18:16.168
THERE'S AN UPSTAIRS WINDOW.

18:16.388 --> 18:19.425
ALL YOU NEEDED
WAS A LADDER TO ESCAPE.

18:20.809 --> 18:24.222
ALICE, WHAT ARE
YOU NOT TELLING ME?

18:29.901 --> 18:34.395
THIS WAS THE ONLY PHOTO
THAT RAY KEPT FROM BEFORE.

18:34.614 --> 18:36.991
THOSE ARE HIS PARENTS.

18:37.200 --> 18:40.988
HE LIVED IN BOSTON.
HIS NAME WAS...

18:43.081 --> 18:45.823
...OSCAR ARNESTO.

18:46.001 --> 18:47.491
WHY'D HE
CHANGE HIS NAME?

18:47.711 --> 18:51.329
HE WORKED FOR THE
DEPANZO CRIME FAMILY FOR YEARS.

18:53.174 --> 18:55.039
BUT HE HAD A FALLING OUT
WITH THEM ABOUT 11 YEARS AGO,

18:55.260 --> 18:57.876
AND HE FLED
WITH SOME OF THEIR MONEY.

18:58.096 --> 19:00.212
I MET HIM IN TEXAS.

19:00.432 --> 19:04.766
AND I JUST --
I JUST FELL IN LOVE WITH HIM.

19:04.978 --> 19:08.266
AFTER WE WERE MARRIED,
HE TOLD ME HIS SECRET.

19:08.481 --> 19:11.063
WHY NOT MAKE A DEAL
WITH THE FEDS,

19:11.276 --> 19:13.983
GET SOME KIND
OF WITNESS PROTECTION?

19:14.195 --> 19:16.811
[ SCOFFS ]
RAY DIDN'T TRUST THE FBI.

19:17.032 --> 19:20.195
WE JUST
WANTED A NORMAL LIFE.

19:20.410 --> 19:22.071
WE BOUGHT THIS RANCH
AND THE HORSES

19:22.287 --> 19:23.572
FOUR YEARS AGO
TO BLEND IN.

19:23.788 --> 19:25.324
SO ALL THIS
IS A COVER.

19:25.540 --> 19:28.031
PAID CASH,
EVERYTHING IN YOUR NAME

19:28.251 --> 19:30.867
SO RAY COULDN'T
LEAVE A PAPER TRAIL.

19:31.087 --> 19:32.702
YEAH.

19:32.922 --> 19:35.789
I GUESS WE WERE JUST
KIDDING OURSELVES.

19:36.009 --> 19:39.376
YOU CAN'T HIDE
FROM THE DEPANZO FAMILY FOREVER.

19:39.596 --> 19:41.336
YOU THINK
THEY KILLED RAY?

19:41.556 --> 19:43.421
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO BELIEVE.

19:43.642 --> 19:44.722
EITHER THEY DID,

19:44.934 --> 19:46.890
OR THEY DROVE RAY
TO KILL HIMSELF.

19:47.103 --> 19:48.309
I DON'T KNOW.

19:48.521 --> 19:52.639
ALICE, NOW,
YOU NEED PROTECTION.

19:52.859 --> 19:55.271
YOU SHOULD COME BACK
TO THE STATION WITH ME.

19:55.487 --> 19:57.148
WE'LL GET T.J.
FROM PRACTICE.

19:57.364 --> 20:00.982
RAY SAID DON'T TRUST THE POLICE,
NO MATTER WHAT.

20:01.201 --> 20:03.908
NO, HE SAID THE MOB
OWNS THE COPS.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.576
YOU THINK
I'M WITH THE MOB?

20:05.789 --> 20:08.906
I DON'T KNOW
THAT YOU'RE NOT.

20:09.084 --> 20:11.040
YOU CAN'T STOP THEM.

20:11.252 --> 20:12.458
LOOK, I'VE TOLD YOU
EVERYTHING THAT I KNOW.

20:12.671 --> 20:16.163
NOW, PLEASE, JUST GO!

20:20.428 --> 20:21.929
SO,
YOU WON'T COME WITH ME?

20:22.138 --> 20:23.594
NO, I CAN'T.

20:25.642 --> 20:26.927
OKAY.

20:27.143 --> 20:28.553
I DON'T HAVE
ANY CHOICE.

20:28.770 --> 20:29.930
ALICE STEWART...

20:32.273 --> 20:34.559
...YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

20:34.776 --> 20:37.438
[SIGHS]

20:44.994 --> 20:48.077
ANY WORD FROM DOC BLOOMFIELD
ON THE AUTOPSY?

20:48.289 --> 20:50.701
NO,
BUT THIS JUST IN.

20:50.917 --> 20:53.078
"SHERIFF LONGMIRE
ARRESTED ALICE STEWART

20:53.294 --> 20:54.704
"AND IS HOLDING HER
FOR QUESTIONING

20:54.921 --> 20:56.502
"IN THE EVENTS
RELATED TO THE BARN FIRE

20:56.715 --> 20:58.296
THAT KILLED HER HUSBAND,
RAY STEWART."

20:58.508 --> 21:00.499
YOU TOLD A REPORTER
BEFORE YOU TOLD US, WALT.

21:00.719 --> 21:02.505
NOPE.

21:02.721 --> 21:04.507
WELL, THEN HOW THE HELL
DID HE FIND OUT?

21:04.723 --> 21:07.339
I GUESS HE'S
A PRETTY GOOD REPORTER.

21:07.559 --> 21:09.515
WHEN WERE YOU GONNA TELL US
YOU ARRESTED HER?

21:09.728 --> 21:11.684
RIGHT AFTER I GAVE HER
HER BREAKFAST.

21:11.896 --> 21:15.104
WALT. WE'RE UNDERSTAFFED
ENOUGH AS IT IS.

21:15.316 --> 21:17.272
IF YOU'RE GONNA FREEZE ME OUT
OF EVERY INVESTIGATION WE GOT

21:17.485 --> 21:18.565
JUST CAUSE I'M RUNNING
AGAINST YOU --

21:18.778 --> 21:19.858
I'M NOT
FREEZING YOU OUT.

21:20.071 --> 21:22.062
I LET YOU CALL
YOUR HANDWRITING EXPERT.

21:22.282 --> 21:25.695
WALT, THIS MAKES
ALL OF US LOOK BAD.

21:25.910 --> 21:27.696
LOOK, ONCE I GOT UPSTAIRS
TO THE OFFICE,

21:27.912 --> 21:29.527
I HAD EVERY INTENTION
OF FILLING YOU IN

21:29.748 --> 21:31.329
AND ASKING FOR HELP.

21:31.541 --> 21:32.872
BUT IF YOU CAN'T WAIT
FIVE MINUTES --
WE CAN'T.

21:33.084 --> 21:34.460
FINE.

21:34.669 --> 21:36.205
BRANCH, I NEED YOU
TO CHECK THE GUEST REGISTRIES

21:36.421 --> 21:37.752
OF ALL THE LOCAL HOTELS
AND GUEST RANCHES.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.704
WALT, COME ON, MAN.

21:39.924 --> 21:41.539
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE A LITTLE MORE
EXCITED TO BE THE ONE LOOKING

21:41.760 --> 21:43.421
INTO A POSSIBLE ORGANIZED-CRIME
CONNECTION TO THIS CASE.

21:43.636 --> 21:45.422
THE PAPER DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT ORGANIZED CRIME.

21:45.638 --> 21:48.050
MUST BE THE FIRST TIME THE PRESS
DIDN'T GET THE WHOLE STORY.

21:48.266 --> 21:50.257
WE'RE LOOKING FOR ANYBODY
FROM THE EAST COAST,

21:50.477 --> 21:52.263
ESPECIALLY BOSTON.

21:52.479 --> 21:55.937
CAN YOU GET THE DOOR?
HEY, WALT,
I GOT TO TELL YOU,

21:56.149 --> 21:58.140
I REALLY DON'T LIKE
FINDING OUT STUFF LIKE THIS

21:58.359 --> 21:59.439
IN THE PAPER.

21:59.652 --> 22:01.938
DO WHAT I DO.
DON'T READ THE PAPER.

22:03.490 --> 22:05.981
YOU'VE BEEN BUSY.

22:06.201 --> 22:07.987
I SEE YOU ARRESTED
A DISTRAUGHT WIDOW

22:08.203 --> 22:10.410
WITHOUT ANYTHING
EVEN APPROACHING PROBABLE CAUSE

22:10.622 --> 22:12.453
AND LEFT HER TRAUMATIZED SON
ALL ALONE.

22:12.665 --> 22:13.916
I DIDN'T
LEAVE HIM ALONE.

22:14.083 --> 22:15.823
I HAD A NEIGHBOR
COME GET HIM.

22:16.044 --> 22:18.000
OH, RIGHT -- BILL HOBACK,
THE MAN WHO'S BEEN

22:18.213 --> 22:20.420
ON THE PHONE ALL MORNING
WITH MY BOSS.

22:20.632 --> 22:22.042
HOBACK CALLED A LAWYER
FOR ALICE?

22:22.258 --> 22:24.840
DAD. [ SIGHS ]

22:25.053 --> 22:27.135
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT A KNEE-JERK,

22:27.347 --> 22:30.510
WRONGFUL ARREST IS THE BEST WAY
TO KICK OFF YOUR CAMPAIGN?

22:30.725 --> 22:31.931
DOESN'T MATTER,
I GUESS,

22:32.143 --> 22:34.008
BECAUSE IF YOU KEEP
ALICE STEWART HERE,

22:34.229 --> 22:35.969
YOU'LL PROBABLY BE SUED,
IT'LL BE IN THE PAPERS,

22:36.189 --> 22:37.304
AND YOU'LL
LOSE THE ELECTION.

22:37.524 --> 22:39.640
I THINK HER LIFE
MIGHT BE IN DANGER.

22:39.859 --> 22:42.692
SO YOU'RE KEEPING HER IN JAIL
FOR HER OWN PROTECTION?

22:42.904 --> 22:44.519
THAT'S --
THAT'S VERY NOBLE.

22:44.739 --> 22:47.401
IT'S ALSO
KIND OF ILLEGAL.

22:47.617 --> 22:49.403
DAD.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

22:49.619 --> 22:52.156
UNLESS YOU CAN COME UP
WITH SOME REAL EVIDENCE

22:52.372 --> 22:54.408
AGAINST HER,
YOU HAVE TO LET HER GO.

22:54.624 --> 22:56.615
[SIGHS]

22:56.835 --> 22:59.542
WOW.
LOOK AT THAT FACE.

22:59.754 --> 23:02.166
YOU REALLY HATE IT
WHEN I'M RIGHT, DON'T YOU?

23:02.382 --> 23:03.838
[CHUCKLES]
[LAUGHS]

23:09.722 --> 23:11.223
[ DOOR OPENS ]

23:11.432 --> 23:13.639
I TELL YOU, WALT, THIS IS NOT
THE KIND OF SHERIFFING

23:13.852 --> 23:17.265
ABSAROKA COUNTY
NEEDS.

23:17.480 --> 23:20.187
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

23:20.400 --> 23:21.981
LOOK AFTER THEM,
BILL.

23:22.193 --> 23:24.605
THEY'LL BE FINE.
THEY'LL BE AT MY PLACE.

23:28.575 --> 23:30.907
HEY, T.J.

23:31.119 --> 23:33.906
IF YOU WANT TO SEE YOUR HORSE,
JUST LET ME KNOW.

23:34.122 --> 23:35.202
I CAN BRING YOU BY.

23:35.415 --> 23:37.326
SO I CAN SEE HER
IN PAIN?
T.J., PLEASE.

23:37.542 --> 23:40.284
DON'T GIVE UP ON HER.
SHE HASN'T.

23:40.503 --> 23:41.458
LET'S JUST GO.

23:45.174 --> 23:47.085
THAT IS ONE CARING
AND ATTENTIVE NEIGHBOR.

23:47.302 --> 23:48.792
YEAH.

23:49.012 --> 23:51.503
WHY DON'T YOU FOLLOW THEM,
SEE THEY GET TO HOBACK'S SAFELY?

23:51.723 --> 23:53.384
MAKE SURE THEY DON'T
RUN OFF TOGETHER.

23:53.600 --> 23:55.215
I'LL SEE YOU
AT DOC BLOOMFIELD'S AFTER.

23:55.435 --> 23:57.426
HEY, RUBY.
UH-HUH?

23:57.645 --> 23:59.510
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
CADY WAS WAITING IN MY OFFICE.

23:59.731 --> 24:00.811
YOU DIDN'T ASK.

24:01.024 --> 24:03.436
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

24:03.651 --> 24:05.858
I FOLLOWED THEM BACK
TO HOBACK'S PLACE, WALT.

24:06.070 --> 24:07.059
NO PROBLEMS.

24:07.280 --> 24:08.690
THEN I CALLED
DOC BLOOMFIELD'S OFFICE.

24:08.907 --> 24:10.067
HE HASN'T EVEN
FINISHED THE AUTOPSY YET.

24:10.283 --> 24:11.272
HE'S BEEN
DELIVERING TWINS ALL DAY.

24:11.492 --> 24:12.868
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT CRAP?

24:13.077 --> 24:15.113
SOME PEOPLE GOT
THEIR PRIORITIES ALL MESSED UP.

24:15.330 --> 24:16.911
I ALSO CHECKED
WITH A FRIEND OF MINE

24:17.123 --> 24:18.738
WHO WORKS ORGANIZED CRIME
BACK EAST.

24:18.958 --> 24:21.574
HE CONFIRMED THAT THERE WAS
AN OSCAR ARNESTO

24:21.794 --> 24:23.625
WHO DISAPPEARED
11 YEARS AGO.

24:23.838 --> 24:26.375
YOUR BUDDY THINK RAY AND OSCAR
ARE THE SAME PERSON?

24:26.591 --> 24:28.547
HE E-MAILED A PICTURE
TO MY CELLPHONE.

24:28.760 --> 24:30.170
IT LOOKS LIKE RAY.

24:30.386 --> 24:31.762
I COULD SEND IT
TO YOUR CELLPH--

24:31.971 --> 24:33.836
OH, WAIT, NO, I CAN'T.
YOU DON'T HAVE A CELL--

24:34.057 --> 24:36.639
[RADIO TURNS OFF]

24:45.568 --> 24:47.274
I'M AGENT DAXNER.
AAH!

24:47.487 --> 24:49.227
OH.

24:49.447 --> 24:53.941
UH, YOU MUST BE THE, UH,
HANDWRITING ANALYST.

24:54.160 --> 24:55.900
FEDERAL MARSHAL.

24:58.706 --> 25:00.742
I WAS HOPING TO HAVE A TALK
WITH YOUR SHERIFF

25:00.959 --> 25:02.620
ABOUT THIS
RAY STEWART SITUATION.

25:02.835 --> 25:04.917
WELL, THE SHERIFF
WON'T BE BACK FOR A WHILE.

25:05.129 --> 25:09.623
I'M FERG--
[SIGHS] DEPUTY FERGUSON.

25:09.842 --> 25:11.378
SOMEONE TOLD ME
TO MEET HIM HERE.

25:11.594 --> 25:14.802
MAYBE THAT WAS RUBY?
UH, SHE'S OUT.

25:15.014 --> 25:18.097
BUT YOU'RE WELCOME
TO WAIT.

25:20.395 --> 25:21.430
YOU WOULDN'T MIND
IF I HAD A WORD

25:21.646 --> 25:22.601
WITH MRS. STEWART,
WOULD YOU?

25:22.814 --> 25:24.054
YOU ARE STILL
HOLDING HER HERE?

25:24.273 --> 25:25.479
I'M SORRY.

25:25.692 --> 25:26.727
SHE -- SHE WAS RELEASED
A COUPLE HOURS AGO.

25:26.943 --> 25:27.932
YOU SENT HER HOME?

25:31.072 --> 25:33.358
SHE --
SHE'S AT A NEIGHBOR'S HOUSE --

25:33.574 --> 25:35.155
UH, BILL HOBACK.

25:35.368 --> 25:36.858
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU RELEASED HER.

25:37.954 --> 25:40.036
[SIGHS]

25:40.248 --> 25:41.909
YOU SHOULD HAVE
CALLED US.

25:43.710 --> 25:46.326
LISTEN...

25:46.546 --> 25:48.537
I WOULD REALLY APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU COULD JUST TELL ME

25:48.756 --> 25:50.292
WHERE I CAN FIND
THE SHERIFF.

25:50.508 --> 25:52.590
HE'S AT THE HOSPITAL
FOR THE AUTOPSY --

25:52.802 --> 25:54.463
JUST ABOUT
15 MINUTES AWAY.

25:54.679 --> 25:55.759
IT'S NEAR
THE GOLF COURSE.

25:55.972 --> 25:56.961
I'LL JUST
MEET HIM THERE, THEN.

26:01.811 --> 26:03.347
FERG LEFT WORD.

26:03.563 --> 26:05.770
A FEDERAL MARSHAL'S HEADING OVER
TO ASK YOU A FEW QUESTIONS.

26:05.982 --> 26:07.188
I BETTER WORK FAST.

26:07.400 --> 26:09.812
WE'RE GONNA LOSE ALL CONTROL
OVER THIS CASE.

26:10.028 --> 26:12.644
WHAT IS THIS,
DOCTOR'S NOTES?

26:12.864 --> 26:13.899
YOU CAN'T
READ A DAMN THING.

26:16.409 --> 26:19.276
UGH.

26:21.122 --> 26:23.158
UGH,
I HATE BURNED BODIES.

26:23.374 --> 26:25.581
IT'S SO HARD
TO MAKE OUT WHAT'S WHAT.

26:25.793 --> 26:27.499
I'VE NEVER SEEN
BURNS LIKE THIS.

26:27.712 --> 26:30.294
HEAT MUST HAVE BEEN
LIKE A SMELT FURNACE.

26:32.467 --> 26:33.422
HUH.

26:34.594 --> 26:38.462
I-I WORKED A SUICIDE
BACK EAST.

26:38.681 --> 26:40.888
SAME SORT OF GUN --
A .45 TO THE SIDE OF THE HEAD,

26:41.100 --> 26:42.715
JUST LIKE THIS.

26:42.935 --> 26:45.096
EXCEPT THERE WAS
NO EXIT WOUND.

26:47.857 --> 26:50.348
THIS GUY'S GOT AN EXIT WOUND,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

26:50.568 --> 26:52.684
MAYBE SOMEBODY ELSE SHOT HIM
WITH A DIFFERENT GUN,

26:52.904 --> 26:54.269
DROPPED THE .45
AT THE SCENE.

27:02.955 --> 27:04.240
NOPE.

27:04.457 --> 27:06.038
HE WAS SHOT
WITH A .45.

27:08.377 --> 27:10.459
[SIGHS]

27:10.671 --> 27:12.411
[SNIFFS]

27:14.217 --> 27:16.708
I THINK I KNOW
WHAT THE ACCELERANT WAS

27:16.928 --> 27:20.546
THAT BURNED HIM THIS BADLY,
HELPED THAT FIRE ALONG.

27:20.765 --> 27:22.175
WHAT?

27:22.391 --> 27:24.382
FORMALDEHYDE.

27:26.145 --> 27:28.477
[GRUNTS]

27:30.733 --> 27:32.234
"A COWARD DIES
MANY DEATHS.

27:32.443 --> 27:37.233
THE VALIANT TASTE
OF DEATH BUT ONCE."

27:37.448 --> 27:39.188
[ COFFIN CREAKS ]

27:46.332 --> 27:48.914
PARDON MY FRENCH,
BUT WHAT THE F...

27:49.127 --> 27:51.243
[SIGHS]

27:53.548 --> 27:55.834
THE REASON
A .45-CALIBER ROUND

27:56.050 --> 27:58.792
DOESN'T LEAVE AN EXIT WOUND
IN THE HEAD

27:59.011 --> 28:00.626
IS BECAUSE THE BRAIN
IS GELATINOUS.

28:00.847 --> 28:02.963
IT SLOWS DOWN
THE BULLET.

28:03.182 --> 28:05.138
BUT IF THE BRAIN TISSUE
WASN'T THERE

28:05.351 --> 28:07.262
OR SHRUNK DOWN
AS HAPPENS TO A BODY

28:07.478 --> 28:09.890
BEEN DEAD FOR A FEW YEARS,
BIG OLD EXIT WOUND.

28:10.106 --> 28:11.141
AND WHY THE HELL DIDN'T YOU
JUST TELL ME THIS

28:11.357 --> 28:12.437
BACK AT THE HOSPITAL?

28:12.650 --> 28:16.939
WASN'T 100% SURE
BACK AT THE HOSPITAL.

28:19.157 --> 28:22.240
[BOTH GRUNT]

28:22.451 --> 28:25.659
SO OUR BURN VICTIM
IS NOT RAY STEWART?

28:25.872 --> 28:28.079
NOPE.
IT'S WILL JACKSON.

28:28.291 --> 28:30.247
AND HOW DID YOU KNOW
TO DIG HERE?

28:30.459 --> 28:34.452
I REMEMBERED SEEING THIS
OLD FAMILY CEMETERY YESTERDAY.

28:34.672 --> 28:36.082
WILL'S BEEN DEAD
FIVE YEARS.

28:36.299 --> 28:38.381
FIGURED RAY WOULD GO
FOR THE FRESHEST BODY.

28:38.593 --> 28:41.881
THEN WE'RE NOT DEALING
WITH A MURDER OR A SUICIDE.

28:42.096 --> 28:45.930
NOPE. WE'VE GOT
A MISSING PERSON.

28:52.940 --> 28:55.101
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

28:59.030 --> 29:02.488
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

29:05.536 --> 29:07.242
WALT: LOOKS LIKE
THEY'RE STILL HERE.

29:07.455 --> 29:08.786
THAT'S HOBACK'S TRUCK.

29:08.998 --> 29:11.410
YOU THINK ALICE KNOWS
HER HUSBAND IS REALLY ALIVE?

29:11.626 --> 29:12.991
MAYBE SHE WAS
IN ON THIS.

29:13.211 --> 29:14.747
NOTHING SURPRISES ME
ANYMORE.

29:14.962 --> 29:16.168
[GUNSHOTS]

29:16.380 --> 29:18.371
I STAND CORRECTED.

29:18.591 --> 29:20.081
[GUNHRE]

29:23.763 --> 29:26.049
BILL: SHERIFF,
YOU BETTER GO AWAY!

29:26.265 --> 29:27.425
HEY, BILL!

29:27.642 --> 29:29.132
I THINK YOU ACCIDENTALLY
LET THE SAFETY OFF

29:29.352 --> 29:30.967
THAT GUN OF YOURS!

29:31.187 --> 29:32.848
SERIOUSLY, WALT!

29:33.064 --> 29:34.895
JUST GET OUT OF HERE,
DRIVE AWAY!

29:35.107 --> 29:38.895
I CAN'T DO THAT, BILL.
YOU FIRED A WEAPON AT ME.

29:39.111 --> 29:42.319
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TOSS THAT GUN OUT THE DOOR?

29:43.950 --> 29:45.611
[GUNSHOT]

29:45.826 --> 29:46.815
AAH!

29:47.036 --> 29:48.401
I THOUGHT YOU
FOLLOWED THEM HOME.

29:48.621 --> 29:49.906
YOU SAID
EVERYTHING WAS NORMAL.

29:50.122 --> 29:51.623
EVERYTHING WAS.
I SAW THE THREE OF THEM GO IN.

29:51.832 --> 29:52.958
I HUNG OUT FOR LIKE
HALF AN HOUR.

29:53.167 --> 29:54.748
NOBODY CAME OUT,
NOBODY WENT IN.

29:54.961 --> 29:56.997
I GUESS WE GOT TO ASSUME

29:57.213 --> 30:00.000
THAT ALICE AND T.J.
ARE IN THERE WITH BILL.

30:00.216 --> 30:01.376
AND MAYBE RAY, TOO.

30:01.592 --> 30:03.674
YOU KNOW,
IF WE WERE BACK EAST,

30:03.886 --> 30:06.127
WE'D CLOSE THE ROADS,
EVACUATE A THREE-BLOCK RADIUS,

30:06.347 --> 30:07.587
AND CALL IN
A S.W.A.T. TEAM.

30:07.807 --> 30:09.013
WELL,
WE DON'T HAVE S.W.A.T.

30:10.643 --> 30:12.759
BUT WE DO HAVE THE FERG.

30:12.979 --> 30:14.185
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

30:24.615 --> 30:26.025
GET DOWN!

30:26.242 --> 30:27.857
[GUNSHOTS]

30:31.289 --> 30:34.452
SHERIFF, I'M SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY.

30:34.667 --> 30:36.749
FOR WHAT, FERG?

30:36.961 --> 30:38.667
THE FEDERAL MARSHAL
WHO WAS SUPPOSED TO
MEET WITH YOU GUYS --

30:38.879 --> 30:40.289
WELL, VIC SAID HE NEVER
SHOWED UP AT THE AUTOPSY.

30:40.506 --> 30:42.497
SO I CALLED THE NUMBER
ON HIS BUSINESS CARD.

30:42.717 --> 30:44.082
AND NO ANSWER.

30:44.302 --> 30:46.418
AND WHEN I CALLED
THE MAIN MARSHAL OFFICE,

30:46.637 --> 30:49.504
THEY SAID -- THEY SAID
THEY'D NEVER EVEN HEARD OF HIM.

30:50.766 --> 30:52.097
THE MARSHAL WAS A FRAUD?

30:52.310 --> 30:53.971
WHAT EXACTLY DID THIS GUY
SAY TO YOU, FERG?

30:54.186 --> 30:56.177
HE WAS LOOKING
FOR ALICE STEWART.

30:56.397 --> 30:57.512
[SIGHS]

30:59.650 --> 31:03.609
I'M THINKING HE FOUND HER.
YOU GET BRANCH OVER HERE.

31:04.822 --> 31:06.528
WE'RE GONNA
NEED SOME BACKUP.

31:08.159 --> 31:10.150
BRANCH: RAY'S ALIVE?

31:10.369 --> 31:12.155
[GUNSHOTS]
IS HE THE ONE
SHOOTING AT US?

31:12.371 --> 31:14.236
I DON'T KNOW.

31:14.457 --> 31:16.948
COULD BE A HIT MAN
POSING AS A FEDERAL MARSHAL.

31:17.168 --> 31:18.704
AND FERG TOLD HIM
WHERE TO GO.

31:19.545 --> 31:21.081
ACCIDENTALLY.

31:21.297 --> 31:25.131
HEY, WALT, WHY DON'T I
CALL THE RES, GET MORE BACKUP?

31:25.343 --> 31:27.629
THAT'LL ONLY
MAKE A TOUGH SITUATION WORSE.

31:27.845 --> 31:29.961
MORE GUNS MAKE IT TOUGH
TO NEGOTIATE.

31:30.181 --> 31:32.797
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS?
A NEGOTIATION?

31:38.105 --> 31:40.391
LET'S FIND OUT.

31:43.986 --> 31:45.146
SHERIFF.

31:46.364 --> 31:49.822
YOU GOT SOMEBODY IN THERE
WHO CALLS HIMSELF AGENT DAXNER?

31:50.034 --> 31:56.280
YOU MAKE SURE AGENT DAXNER KNOWS
MY NUMBER-ONE PRIORITY HERE

31:56.499 --> 31:57.488
IS NOBODY GETS HURT.

32:12.932 --> 32:15.218
GET IT OFF!

32:15.434 --> 32:17.049
GET IT OFF!

32:17.269 --> 32:20.636
GET IT OFF!
GET IT OFF!

32:20.856 --> 32:23.347
[ PANTING, GROANING ]

32:25.027 --> 32:26.528
WALT:
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

32:26.737 --> 32:28.944
THAT GUY, DAXNER,

32:29.156 --> 32:30.987
HE SAID HE WAS
LOOKING FOR ALICE.

32:31.200 --> 32:34.408
HE SAID HE WAS A MARSHAL,
SO I OPENED THE DOOR,

32:34.620 --> 32:36.235
AND HE JUST WENT CRAZY.

32:36.455 --> 32:38.286
ARE ALICE AND T.J. OKAY?

32:38.499 --> 32:39.579
OH, THEY'RE SCARED.

32:39.792 --> 32:41.282
THEY'RE JUST --
THIS GUY'S CRAZY.

32:41.502 --> 32:43.163
WHAT DOES HE WANT?

32:43.379 --> 32:45.665
HE SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
WANTING THE MONEY

32:45.881 --> 32:47.132
THAT RAY STOLE FROM HIM.

32:47.341 --> 32:50.299
BUT HE -- HE KEPT
CALLING RAY "OSCAR."

32:50.511 --> 32:51.921
SO, WHAT IS GOING ON?

32:52.138 --> 32:55.096
SO DAXNER DOESN'T KNOW
THAT RAY'S ACTUALLY STILL ALIVE?

32:55.307 --> 32:56.968
NO.

32:59.520 --> 33:00.805
[SIGHS]

33:01.021 --> 33:04.309
BUT YOU DO, OBVIOUSLY.

33:05.860 --> 33:07.316
DOES ALICE KNOW?

33:07.528 --> 33:09.064
NO.

33:10.739 --> 33:12.240
HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN
RAY FAKED HIS DEATH?

33:13.826 --> 33:16.533
SINCE THE NIGHT
OF THE FIRE.

33:16.745 --> 33:19.737
WHEN I CAME HOME THAT NIGHT,
HE WAS HERE.

33:19.957 --> 33:24.166
HE, UH -- HE SAID HE SET
THE FIRE TO PROTECT HIS FAMILY.

33:24.378 --> 33:26.084
BUT HE WOULDN'T TELL ME
MORE THAN THAT.

33:27.965 --> 33:30.456
JESUS, WALT,
YOU GOT TO UNDERSTAND.

33:30.676 --> 33:32.462
RAY'S --
HE'S BEEN A GOOD FRIEND.

33:32.678 --> 33:35.294
HE SAVED MY BUSINESS
A COUPLE YEARS AGO, AND,

33:35.514 --> 33:36.845
YOU KNOW, I OWED HIM.

33:38.434 --> 33:40.766
WHERE IS HE NOW?
I DON'T KNOW.

33:40.978 --> 33:42.434
I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM
SINCE THAT NIGHT.

33:42.646 --> 33:43.931
JUST TALKED TO HIM
ON THE PHONE.

33:44.148 --> 33:47.185
RAY'S CELLPHONE
WAS DESTROYED IN THE FIRE.

33:47.401 --> 33:48.311
I GAVE HIM MINE.

33:50.779 --> 33:52.110
AND THAT'S IT.

33:52.323 --> 33:55.030
THAT'S -- THAT'S THE TRUTH,
WALT. I SWEAR TO YOU.

33:55.242 --> 33:57.779
BRANCH: HE'S LYING.

33:57.995 --> 34:00.202
PHONE COMPANY TOLD ME EXACTLY
HOW FAR HOBACK'S CELLPHONE IS

34:00.414 --> 34:01.369
FROM THE NEAREST CELL TOWER.

34:01.582 --> 34:02.662
THE CELL TOWER IS HERE,

34:02.875 --> 34:06.163
WHICH MEANS THAT PHONE
IS ON THIS LINE.

34:06.378 --> 34:07.993
THAT'S RIGHT HERE.
EXACTLY.

34:08.214 --> 34:09.624
HOBACK'S PHONE
IS INSIDE HIS HOUSE.

34:09.840 --> 34:12.047
SO EITHER HOBACK
NEVER GAVE RAY THE CELL, OR --

34:12.259 --> 34:13.465
RAY'S NOT IN THE HOUSE,
WALT.

34:13.677 --> 34:16.168
I SWEAR TO YOU.
I TOLD YOU THE TRUTH.

34:18.265 --> 34:19.926
THIS WEATHER SUCKS.

34:20.142 --> 34:22.633
YEAH.

34:28.984 --> 34:31.851
BRANCH,
GIVE ME A MINUTE.

34:32.071 --> 34:33.686
DO SOMETHING
TO DRAW ATTENTION TO YOURSELF.

34:33.906 --> 34:36.693
YOU'RE GOOD AT THAT.

34:50.673 --> 34:52.584
[GUNSHOTS]

34:52.800 --> 34:56.258
[GUNHRE]

35:11.277 --> 35:13.233
[GUNHRE]

35:19.493 --> 35:23.782
RAY,
YOU AND I NEED TO TALK.

35:23.998 --> 35:27.536
OR SHOULD I
CALL YOU OSCAR?

35:35.009 --> 35:37.250
JUST -- JUST LET ME EXPLAIN,
WALT. OKAY, JUST LET ME EXPLAIN.

35:37.469 --> 35:39.755
NOBODY'S
TRYING TO STOP YOU.
ALL RIGHT.

35:41.974 --> 35:44.681
THEY WERE
COMING FOR ME.

35:44.893 --> 35:46.224
THEY WERE.

35:46.437 --> 35:48.803
TWO WEEKS AGO I WAS IN TOWN,
AND I SAW LENDETTA.

35:49.023 --> 35:50.354
WHO'S LENDETTA?

35:50.566 --> 35:52.932
LENDETTA'S
ONE OF DEPANZO'S GUYS.

35:53.152 --> 35:56.269
HE'S PROBABLY IN TOWN
TRYING TO WORK SOMETHING OUT

35:56.488 --> 35:57.989
WITH THE NEW CASINO.

35:58.198 --> 36:00.814
I SAW HIM IN THE STREET,
AND H KNOW HE SAW ME, WALT.

36:01.035 --> 36:02.150
I-I KNOW HE DID.

36:02.369 --> 36:04.075
[ BANGING ]
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

36:04.288 --> 36:05.277
WHO'S THE GUY UPSTAIRS?

36:05.497 --> 36:08.489
PROBABLY
ONE OF THEIR HIT MEN.

36:08.709 --> 36:12.076
WHY NOT JUST TAKE YOUR MOB MONEY
AND GET OUT OF ABSAROKA COUNTY?

36:12.296 --> 36:14.036
THAT MONEY'S GONE,
WALT.

36:15.633 --> 36:18.716
I NEEDED THAT INSURANCE MONEY
JUST TO SURVIVE.

36:18.927 --> 36:21.339
I HAD NO CHOICE.
CAN'T YOU SEE THAT?

36:21.555 --> 36:24.888
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT I SEE.
I SEE A HORSE MURDERER.

36:25.100 --> 36:27.807
I SEE A GRAVE ROBBER.

36:28.020 --> 36:31.262
I SEE A MAN WHOSE WIFE
AND SON ARE UPSTAIRS

36:31.482 --> 36:35.066
WITH A GUN TO THEIR HEADS
WHILE HE'S DOWNSTAIRS,

36:35.277 --> 36:37.893
WARM AND SAFE.

36:38.113 --> 36:39.444
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

36:39.657 --> 36:41.989
I CAME BACK HERE
FOR THEM, WALT.

36:42.201 --> 36:45.193
I CAME BACK
TO TAKE THEM WITH ME!

36:45.412 --> 36:47.528
BUT HE
WAS HERE FIRST.

36:47.748 --> 36:49.409
[ INDISTINCT TALKING
IN DISTANCE ]

36:49.625 --> 36:54.244
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

36:54.463 --> 36:56.545
BUT I AIN'T NO COWARD.

36:56.757 --> 37:01.421
NOW, YOU JUST GIVE ME A CHANCE,
AND I CAN FIX THIS.

37:01.637 --> 37:04.879
[CRIES]

37:05.099 --> 37:07.590
ALICE:
YOU STILL HAVE A CHOICE.

37:07.810 --> 37:08.925
DAXNER: SHUT UP!

37:09.144 --> 37:11.305
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:11.522 --> 37:14.355
YOU'VE BEEN HIDING OUT
YOUR WHOLE LIFE, RAY.

37:15.609 --> 37:19.898
YOU JUST NEED TO HIDE OUT
A LITTLE LONGER.

37:20.114 --> 37:21.274
WALT.

37:21.490 --> 37:24.106
WALT!

37:28.580 --> 37:30.832
THAT WASN'T EXACTLY
WHAT I HAD IN MIND

37:30.999 --> 37:32.455
AS A DISTRACTION,
BRANCH.

37:32.668 --> 37:34.158
IT WORKED, DIDN'T IT?

37:34.378 --> 37:35.493
IT DID.

37:35.713 --> 37:37.294
ALL RIGHT.

37:37.506 --> 37:38.916
I CAN GET DAXNER
TO LEAVE WITH ME.

37:39.133 --> 37:41.124
ONCEIDO,
YOU GUYS GO INSIDE,

37:41.343 --> 37:44.255
GET ALICE AND T.J.,
MAKE SURE THEY'RE OKAY.

37:44.471 --> 37:46.086
YOU'LL FIND RAY
IN THE CELLAR.

37:46.306 --> 37:48.388
OKAY.
[ SNIFFS ]

37:48.600 --> 37:51.512
DAXN ER! H EY!

37:51.729 --> 37:54.971
SORRY I BEEN GONE
SO LONG,

37:55.190 --> 37:57.977
BUT I THINK YOU'LL APPRECIATE
WHAT I WAS UP TO.

37:58.193 --> 37:59.569
I WAS FINDING YOUR MONEY.

37:59.778 --> 38:01.234
RAY'S MONEY.

38:01.447 --> 38:05.531
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT, RIGHT?
I CAN TAKE YOU TO IT.

38:05.743 --> 38:08.109
ALICE AND THE BOY
DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS.

38:08.328 --> 38:09.488
THEY'RE NO USE TO YOU.

38:09.705 --> 38:13.118
BUT I KNOW.

38:13.333 --> 38:15.119
IF YOU JUST COME WITH ME --

38:15.335 --> 38:18.577
RAY: HEY!
THIS IS OSCAR ARNESTO!

38:18.797 --> 38:21.755
YOU DON'T CARE ABOUT THAT MONEY!
YOU WANT ME!

38:21.967 --> 38:23.252
SO COME DOWN HERE AND GET ME,
YOU SON OF A BITCH!

38:23.469 --> 38:24.959
I AIN'T AFRAID OF YOU!

38:25.179 --> 38:26.419
[GUNHRE]

38:29.933 --> 38:31.764
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

38:45.282 --> 38:46.863
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

39:15.896 --> 39:17.181
[GRUNTS]

39:17.397 --> 39:18.432
[ DAXNER COUGHS]

39:30.160 --> 39:33.448
[ PANTING ]
OH, NO.

39:33.664 --> 39:35.529
[ PANTING ]

39:38.126 --> 39:43.211
WHY DIDN'T YOU
STAY QUIET?

39:43.423 --> 39:46.290
[ WEAKLY ] I TOLD YOU
I WASN'T A COWARD.

40:10.701 --> 40:13.192
I KNOW
I WAS A FAVOR.

40:13.412 --> 40:15.573
I ONLY GOT HIRED 'CAUSE YOU WERE
HELPING OUT MY DAD.

40:17.374 --> 40:23.085
I'M JUST --
I'M NOT CUT OUT FOR THIS.

40:27.509 --> 40:30.216
FERG, I HIRED YOU
FOR TWO REASONS.

40:30.429 --> 40:32.761
YES, ONE WAS A FAVOR
TO YOUR FATHER.

40:32.973 --> 40:34.964
AND THE OTHER?

40:40.939 --> 40:43.021
I'M STILL WAITING
TO FIND OUT.

40:43.233 --> 40:45.645
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

40:49.740 --> 40:51.401
PICK UP YOUR BADGE,
DEPUTY.

40:51.617 --> 40:54.233
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

40:54.453 --> 40:57.445
[MUSIC]

40:57.664 --> 40:58.915
WALT.

40:59.958 --> 41:01.789
VET'S ON THE PHONE.

41:18.644 --> 41:22.387
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
DO THIS ANYMORE.

41:22.606 --> 41:26.315
YOU ALREADY
PROVED HOW TOUGH YOU ARE.

41:30.072 --> 41:32.233
IT'S OKAY TO GO.

41:34.409 --> 41:36.570
IT'S OKAY.

41:55.055 --> 41:56.920
[SIGHS]

41:57.140 --> 42:02.760
"KNOW WHEN TO FIGHT
AND WHEN TO SEEK PEACE.

42:02.980 --> 42:05.596
"FOR AS LONG
AS THE MOON SHALL RISE,

42:05.816 --> 42:08.899
"AS LONG
AS THE RIVERS SHALL FLOW,

42:09.111 --> 42:13.525
"AS LONG AS THE SUN
WILL SHINE,

42:13.740 --> 42:18.074
LET US ALL
KNOW PEACE."

42:20.038 --> 42:22.279
[ HORSE SNORTS ]

42:22.499 --> 42:24.956
[MUSIC CONTINUES]
